    "and can be modified by electrodeposition methods to generate various 3D mesoporous metals 23.",
    "We previously developed an inexpensive and scalable method to deposit mesoporous metals (e.g., Au, Ag, Cu) on conductive 2D electrodes by co-depositing block copolymer micelles (BCM) with metal using a simple electrochemical setup 23.",
    "The size of the mesopores can be tuned from 5 to 40 nm in diameter depending on the diameter of the BCM, and the resulting subwavelength pores interact strongly with light to enable SERS sensing 24, 25.",
    "In an adapted procedure, the commercial 3D silver foam (AgF) was used as the electrode, enabling Ag + and polystyrene 18000 -block-polyethylene oxide 7500 (PS 18000 -b-PEO 7500) BCMs to be co-deposited on the 3D surface (Fig. 2a and Suppl.",
    "According to X-ray microtomography (µ-CT), unmodified AgF have convoluted macroscale features with an average pore diameter of 262 µm with a void space of 84.1% versus the total volume (Fig. 2b and Suppl."
  ]
